  .f-p.container
    .view-f-p.col-md-3.offset-md-1
      .this-face-wrap.mb-5
        %span.badge-base
          %span.badge.center founder
        .this-face
          .face= image_tag @president.avatar.url(:pro), class: "img-circle center"
          %h2.name.mt-3.mb-2
            = @president.name
            - if @president.notes.count >= 5
              %span
                %i.fa.fa-check-circle
          .follow.edit
            - if user_signed_in?
              - if current_user != @president
                - if !current_user.following?(@president)
                  = form_for(current_user.active_relationships.build) do |f|
                    = hidden_field_tag :followed_id, @president.id
                    = f.submit "Follow", class: "btn-std btn-sm btn-follow-edit"
                - else
                  = form_for(current_user.active_relationships.find_by(followed_id: @president.id), html: { method: :delete }) do |f|
                    = f.submit "Unfollow", class: "btn-std btn-sm btn-follow-edit"
              - else
                = link_to "Edit Profile", edit_user_registration_path, class: 'btn-std btn-sm btn-follow-edit'
          %p.has.mt-4.mb-0
            = pluralize(@president.followers.count, "Follower")
            = 'â€¢'
            = pluralize(@president.notes.count, "Note")
          %p.email.mb-0= @president.email
    .text-f-p.col-md-7
      %p.text
        %span.mb-3
          I am extremely delighted to anounce the founding of Mattrab.
          %br
          Welcome to Mattrab Creative Community!
        %span.mb-3.text-justify.t-small
          I believe that every student has ability to understand everything and make other understand. So, why not we actually share what we have understood and help eachother towards the success.
          %br
          Here at mattrab, anybody can create their own notes/resources, explore and sharpen their ability and help many others around simultaneously.
          %br
          I would like to express my sincere thanks to my reverent sir Matt Bubbernak who helped me during all the process of engineering, developing and deploying Mattrab.
        %span
          Good luck everyone! Create, explore and share!
      %p.speaker.mb-5
        %span Rabin K. Kalikote
        Founder and President of Mattrab/Community.
